outcast is a 1928 silent film drama produced and distributed by first national pictures . it was directed by william a. seiter and stars corinne griffith , often considered one of the most beautiful women in film . this story had been filmed in 1917 as the world and the woman with jeanne eagels . in 1922 a paramount film of the same name with elsie ferguson reprising her stage role was released . both films were based on a 1914 play , outcast , by hubert henry davies which starred ferguson . the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; film was an all silent with vitaphone music and sound effects . in the sound era the story was filmed once again as the girl from 10th avenue starring bette davis . according to the library of congress database shows a print surviving complete at cineteca italiana in milan .